arch:property.oc:show_val: Phase XI: Site abandonment after major collapse dating to the Byzantine period from the CE 4th to 5th c. New drainage systems are installed including that associated with the newly built west precinct wall.
Dark soil with collapse south of Locus 39 in the “hypocaust room”

Locus 4 is a layer of dark soil in the "hypocaust room" below Locus 3, an overlting sedimentation and collapse layer. Unlike Locus 3, Locus 4 is confined to the "hypocaust room" and the soil is slightly darker with a Munsell color of 5 YR 5/3, red brown. Locus 4 contains a large amount of plaster inclusions and a medium amount of pottery. The texture of the soil is fine silt and it does ball. This is probably an early sedimentation layer.
5.90 m north south -by- 4.90 m east west.
